profile_positions.description:
Working in the Business Development team of SNV's Global Support Unit in the Hague, supporting prospect development across SNV countries including Nepal, DRC, Laos, Kenya, and Ghana, on Agriculture, Energy, and WASH, for donors such as the World Bank, EU, and Finnish MFA. 

Identifying and assessing forecasts and notices, coordination of lead development and capture planning for tenders, overall pipeline development: 
- supporting SNV country offices on BD (e.g. Internal and donor processes and procedures, assessing opportunities, analyzing donor conditions, and determining SNV's capacity and/or eligibility);
- identifying business opportunities and leads for SNV countries and sectors,
- involvement in improving internal BD processes, decision-making, and support to countries;
- lead development and assessments through analysis and intelligence gathering on upcoming bids;
- capture planning and coordination to position SNV as best as possible for upcoming bids;
- supporting and coordinating development of EOIs and supporting planning for full proposals, working together with an internal prospect team for the technical proposal, financial proposal/budget, and project HR;
- monitoring and administration of data quality on Salesforce, monthly reporting on the organization's pipeline and order intake data, and contracting of consultants;
